==English==
{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
From {{compound|bull|shit}}. In use since the 1920s.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈbʊlʃɪt/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{context|vulgar|slang|lang=en}} False or exaggerated statements made to impress and deceive the listener rather than inform; [[nonsense]].
#: ''Don't pay any attention to him. He talks a lot of '''bullshit'''.''
# {{context|vulgar|slang|lang=en}} A [[card game]] in which the object is to bluff about cards laid down and to determine when one's opponents are bluffing; also known as "BS" or "I Doubt It".
#: ''Anyone want to play a few hands of '''bullshit'''?''
# {{context|vulgar|slang|lang=en}} An object of frustration and/or disgust, often caused by a perceived deception.
#: ''That's '''bullshit'''! I called your office and they said you never came in!''
# {{context|literally|lang=en}} The faeces of a bull.

